<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870106-0146 </DOCNO><HL> RJR Nabisco Unit SeeksTo Sell Certain Operations</HL><DD> 01/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> RJRTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WINSTON-SALEM, N.C.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   R.J. Reynolds Tobacco Co., a unit of RJR Nabisco Inc., said it is holding talks with potential buyers of its loose-tobacco and little-cigar businesses.    Reynolds Tobacco didn't identify the potential buyers. The company said it wants to sell the operations to concentrate on its cigarette business.    The loose-tobacco and little-cigar operations account for about 1% of Reynolds Tobacco's sales, the company said. Reynolds Tobacco had total sales of about $8.1 billion in 1985. </TEXT></DOC>